  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Maintenance Engineer (Facility)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>In charge of conducting maintenance training on machinery and equipment for end users.</li>\n  <li>Responsible for performing preventive maintenance on machinery used in production department.</li>\n  <li>In charge of planning and performing tasks related to facilities, upgrading and repairing machinery and equipment.</li>\n  <li>Responsible for troubleshooting machinery malfunctions.</li>\n  <li>Take charge of maintaining updated records of repairs and completed preventative maintenance work.</li>\n  <li>Responsible for identifying and purchasing critical spares for preventive maintenance.</li>\n  <li>Responsible for identifying probable causes of potential failure of machinery &amp; equipment and arrange for preventive repair and replacement to minimize machine downtime.</li>\n  <li>In charge of maintain good housekeeping practices in maintenance work area and stores.</li>\n  <li>Responsible for ensuring Compliance of in-house safety rules and procedures by all vendors</li>\n  <li>In charge of supervising contractors performing maintenance jobs</li>\n  <li>Perform related duties as assigned.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Job Requirement:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Min Diploma in Electrical/Mechanical/Precision/ Manufacturing Engineering or related discipline.</li>\n  <li>Min 5 years working experience in CNC machines and equipment maintenance and repair works in the manufacturing environment</li>\n</ul>\n<p>To submit your application, please apply online to <strong>apply@rn-care.com </strong>or call <strong>+(65) 6513 5697</strong> for private and confidential discussion.</p>\n<p>Your interest will be treated with the strictest of confidence. We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified or contacted.</p>\n<p><strong>RN Care Pte. Ltd</strong></p>\n<p><strong>EA License No: 17C8900</strong></p>",
